version_description: I wanted to submit the whole song with chords above the words so that it is more easily played using the scroll option. I have also used an set of chords that are best played in DADGAD tuning.

I checked out the other tabs and none of them seemed to have all the right chords, so from the other tabs, an Eagles song book and by listening to the song be played, I'm 99% sure these are the correct chords :)
Capo 2: More original with slight change, but closer to the actual band. Those F#m7 and the F#sus4 make up the featured guitar solos.

version_description: This version has the same chords from Eagles Anthology - Easy Guitar songbook.
Correct key, neat formatting of all lyrics and break with accompanying chords, chord legend incuded.

The chords are very good on version 1 but it's incomplete and hard to follow while playing. I put this together for myself and figured I'd submit it because it's a great Christmas song and I felt a complete version should be on UG.
This version has more chord changes, using slightly more difficult chords.  It was based off the Eagles version, but we used the "glad, glad news" lyric from the Bon Jovi version.
This version uses some different chords and is a little different.
